main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in the sky over San Rafael, California, on August 25, 1953, between 10:30 P.M. and 10:55 P.M.
interesting points: The object appeared to be 'stars thru o'cast', suggesting it may have been a misidentification of celestial objects through cloud cover.
The report indicates the object was observed visually for approximately 25 minutes.
No other details about the object's appearance or behavior are provided.
